[{"ID":219,"title":"Laravel Paymill package","status":"publish","type":"post","author":{"ID":1,"username":"ben","name":"Ben Speakman","first_name":"Ben","last_name":"Speakman","nickname":"ben","slug":"ben","URL":"","avatar":"","description":"","registered":"2011-08-02T23:05:05+00:00","meta":{"links":{"self":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/users\/1","archives":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/users\/1\/posts"}}},"content":"<p>I wrote a Laravel specific wrapper for the <a title=\"Paymill PHP Library\" href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/paymill\/paymill-php\" target=\"_blank\">Paymill PHP Library<\/a>. This package handles the configuration and provides a facade interface to the paymill api with more of a &#8216;Laravel&#8217; style to it.<br \/>\n<!--more--><\/p>\n<codeblock php theme=\"okaidia\" [lineNumbers]=\"false\" class=\"language-php\">try {\r\n\r\n    Paymill::Transaction()\r\n        -&gt;setAmount(4200)\r\n        -&gt;setCurrency('EUR')\r\n        -&gt;setPayment('pay_2f82a672574647cd911d')\r\n        -&gt;setDescription('Test Transaction')\r\n        -&gt;create();\r\n\r\n} catch(PaymillException $e) {\r\n\r\n    $e-&gt;getResponseCode();\r\n    $e-&gt;getStatusCode();\r\n    $e-&gt;getErrorMessage();\r\n\r\n}\r\n<\/codeblock>\n<p>It also shares a variable with the views so you can use your public key like so:<\/p>\n<codeblock php class=\"language-javascript\">&lt;script type=\"text\/javascript\"&gt;\r\n var PAYMILL_PUBLIC_KEY = '{{ $paymill_public_key }}';\r\n&lt;\/script&gt;<\/codeblock>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/threesquared\/laravel-paymill\" target=\"_blank\">Check it out on github<\/a>.<\/p>\n","parent":null,"link":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/2015\/05\/laravel-paymill-package\/","date":"2015-05-02T17:53:29","modified":"2015-05-21T18:03:19","format":"standard","slug":"laravel-paymill-package","guid":"http:\/\/threesquared.net\/blog\/?p=219","excerpt":"<p>I wrote a Laravel specific wrapper for the Paymill PHP Library. This package handles the configuration and provides a facade interface to the paymill api with more of a &#8216;Laravel&#8217; style to it.<\/p>\n","menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"date_tz":"UTC","date_gmt":"2015-05-02T17:53:29","modified_tz":"UTC","modified_gmt":"2015-05-21T18:03:19","meta":{"links":{"self":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/posts\/219","author":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/users\/1","collection":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/posts","replies":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/posts\/219\/comments","version-history":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/posts\/219\/revisions"}},"featured_image":null,"terms":{"category":[{"ID":4,"name":"Projects","slug":"projects","description":"","taxonomy":"category","parent":null,"count":4,"link":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/category\/projects\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms","self":"https:\/\/3sq.re\/blog\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms\/4"}}}]}}]
